index]`, add:\n```tsx\nif (!photo) return null\n```\n\n**I-4: Restore focus to the opener on lightbox close**\n\nFind the `useEffect` that does auto-focus. It currently looks like:\n```tsx\nuseEffect(() => { dialogRef.current?.focus() }, [])\n```\n\nReplace with:\n```tsx\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const opener = document.activeElement as HTMLElement | null\n  dialogRef.current?.focus()\n  return () => { opener?.focus() }\n}, [])\n```\n\n**I-5: Add Tab key focus trap**\n\nIn the existing `useEffect` that registers keyboard events (the one that handles Escape, ArrowLeft, ArrowRight), add Tab trap logic. Replace the entire keyboard `useEffect` with:\n\n```tsx\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const handleKey = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {\n    if (e.key === 'Escape') { onClose(); return }\n    if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') { onPrev(); return }\n    if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') { onNext(); return }\n    if (e.key === 'Tab') {\n      const focusable = dialogRef.current?.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('button')\n      if (!focusable || focusable.length === 0) return\n      const first = focusable[0]\n      const last = focusable[focusable.length - 1]\n      if (e.shiftKey) {\n        if (document.activeElement === first) { e.preventDefault(); last.focus() }\n      } else {\n        if (document.activeElement === last) { e.preventDefault(); first.focus() }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKey)\n  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKey)\n}, [onClose, onPrev, onNext])\n```\n\n---\n\n### After all edits:\n\nRun `cd \"e:/GitProject/awesome-big-V\" && npx tsc --noEmit` then `npm run build` — both must pass.\n\nCommit:\n```bash\ngit add components/home/Hero.tsx app/gallery/page.tsx components/gallery/Lightbox.tsx\ngit commit -m \"fix(a11y): correct heading order, lightbox focus trap and focus restore\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Status reporting:\nEnd with exactly one of:\n- `STATUS: DONE`\n- `STATUS: DONE_WITH_CONCERNS`\n- `STATUS: NEEDS_CONTEXT`\n- `STATUS: 